{
  "texts": [
    "The number of iterations is set equal to 500 times N/K (the number of labeled samples per class).",
    "We used a learning rate of 2 * 10 -4, with a cosine scheduler and a batch size of 32, so that all training could be performed on a single GPU of 24 Gb.",
    "These hyper-parameters are kept fixed across all the experiments.",
    "The input prompt is simply set to a photo of a [kth class name], k = 1,..., K, for every dataset, to emphasize the applicability of CLIP-LoRA without resorting to complex initial manual prompting.",
    "Note that the LoRA modules are positioned at every levels of both encoders."
  ]
}